Germany's Bundesrat votes to ban the internal combustion engine by 2030

Is the tide turning for the internal combustion engine? Over in Germany things are starting to look that way. This is the country that invented the technology, yet late last week the Bundesrat (the federal council of all 16 German states) voted to ban gasoline- and diesel-powered vehicles by 2030.
Jonathan M. Gitlin / Ars Technica
